theorem closure_inter_interior_subset_closure_inter {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X]
    {A B : Set X} :
    (closure (A : Set X) ∩ interior (B : Set X) : Set X) ⊆
      closure ((A : Set X) ∩ B) := by
  intro x hx
  rcases hx with ⟨hxClA, hxIntB⟩
  -- We prove that every open neighborhood of `x` meets `A ∩ B`.
  refine (mem_closure_iff).2 ?_
  intro V hVOpen hxV
  -- Obtain an open neighborhood `U` of `x` contained in `B`.
  rcases hxIntB with ⟨U, hUOpen, hxU, hUsubB⟩
  -- Consider the open set `V ∩ U`.
  have hWOpen : IsOpen ((V ∩ U : Set X)) := hVOpen.inter hUOpen
  have hxW : x ∈ (V ∩ U : Set X) := And.intro hxV hxU
  -- Since `x ∈ closure A`, the set `(V ∩ U) ∩ A` is nonempty.
  have hNon : ((V ∩ U : Set X) ∩ A).Nonempty := by
    have := (mem_closure_iff).1 hxClA (V ∩ U) hWOpen hxW
    simpa using this
  -- Extract a point `y` in the intersection.
  rcases hNon with ⟨y, hy⟩
  rcases hy with ⟨⟨hyV, hyU⟩, hyA⟩
  have hyB : (y : X) ∈ B := hUsubB hyU
  -- Thus `y` lies in `V ∩ (A ∩ B)`.
  have : (V ∩ ((A : Set X) ∩ B)).Nonempty := ⟨y, And.intro hyV ⟨hyA, hyB⟩⟩
  simpa [Set.inter_assoc, Set.inter_left_comm, Set.inter_comm] using this

theorem interior_union_has_all_Ps {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A B : Set X} :
    Topology.P1 (interior ((A ∪ B) : Set X)) ∧
      Topology.P2 (interior ((A ∪ B) : Set X)) ∧
        Topology.P3 (interior ((A ∪ B) : Set X)) := by
  have hOpen : IsOpen (interior ((A ∪ B) : Set X)) := isOpen_interior
  exact
    Topology.isOpen_has_all_Ps
      (X := X) (A := interior ((A ∪ B) : Set X)) hOpen
